The paper focuses on index structures for immutable data, which is a topic related to data structures and databases. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for tamper-evident controls, which is related to security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also evaluates the performance of different index structures, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
